name: Haribo x Suede 'Poppy Red'
story: Releasing as part of a larger collection with the German candy brand, the Haribo x PUMA Suede ‘Poppy Red’ dresses the classic model in a flooded crimson finish. ‘HARIBO’ is stamped on the lateral heel of the soft suede upper, while dual PUMA and Haribo branding lands on the stitched tongue tag and sockliner. The confectioner’s signature Goldbear gummy appears via a molded hangtag, a gel insert on the heel tab, and a subtle graphic print throughout the translucent rubber outsole.

name: Diana Taurasi x LeBron 18 EP 'La Cabra'
adidas Ultra Boost 4.0 DNA White Gold Metallic
adidas Superstar Bold White Ambient Sky (W)
adidas NMD R1 Black Rose Tone (W)
adidas NMD R1 White Ambient Sky (W)
adidas Superstar Trefoil White Purple Tint (W)
adidas Ultra Boost 4.0 DNA Black Silver Metallic
adidas NMD R1 White Halo Blue Shock Pink (W)
Jordan 6 Retro Gold Hoops (W)
story: The women’s Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Gold Hoops’ adds gilded accents to the shoe that Michael Jordan wore when he clinched his first ever NBA championship. The vintage mid-top carries a white tumbled leather upper with Barely Rose hits on the tongue, heel tab and midsole, fitted with a visible Air-sole unit in the heel. Metallic gold lace locks are matched by a trio of earring-inspired gold hoops, with a Jumpman charm attached to the lowest ring via a short gold chain. Underfoot, milky translucent rubber is utilized on the outsole.

name: adidas NMD R1 Wonder White Pulse Yellow Pink (W)
adidas NMD R1 Wonder White Signal Green (W)
KAWHI 'New Money'
story: Taking its design cues from a crisp $100 bill, the New Balance KAWHI ‘New Money’ continues a bankroll-inspired series that began with the ‘Money Stacks’ colorway of the New Balance OMN1S. Kawhi Leonard’s signature shoe features a muted teal upper constructed from mesh with a synthetic forefoot overlay. Gold accents make their way to the sneaker’s Kinetic Stitch quarter panel, a raised NB logo on the prominent heel counter, and ‘100’ stamped atop the tongue. The sneaker rides on a FuelCell foam midsole, supported by a full-length performance plate and a translucent rubber outsole.

name: adidas NMD R1 Crystal White Clear Pink (W)
Reebok Question Low White Clear Blue Sole
story: The Reebok Question Low ‘White Clear’ updates Allen Iverson’s debut signature shoe with a blank-slate finish. Ghillie lacing secures the white leather upper, reinforced with a tonal leather toe cap and accented with a Question logo stamped on the heel tab. Breathable mesh is utilized on the sneaker’s throat, while soft textile lines the low-cut collar. The sneaker rides on a matching white EVA midsole with visible Hexalite cushioning. Underfoot, an icy translucent rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

name: adidas Superstar LEGO White Black
story: The LEGO x adidas Superstar ‘Base Plates’ transforms the iconic sneaker with unique details inspired by the Danish toy brand. The low-top makes use of a synthetic white leather upper made in part with recycled content. Reminiscent of a LEGO baseplate, a studded texture is applied to the sneaker’s rubber toe, as well as the contrasting black heel tab and serrated three-stripes. Dual adidas and LEGO branding adorns the bright yellow sockliner. The low-profile silhouette is mounted a standard rubber cuposle, featuring a herringbone traction pattern underfoot.

name: Air Force 1 '07 LV8 'Coconut Milk Hyper Royal'
Nike Space Hippie 01 Melon Tint Aquamarine
story: Continuing the brand’s exploratory footwear collection predicated on recycling and limited resources, the Nike Space Hippie 01 ‘Melon Tint’ spotlights the speckled Crater Foam midsole — built with a blend of standard foam compounds and Nike Grind rubber — by applying a vibrant orange finish. Up top, the sneaker’s beige knit construction is made with mostly recycled content that includes plastic bottles, T-shirts and post-industrial scraps. A plush insole composed of ZoomX foam scraps delivers a cushioned ride.

name: Nike Space Hippie 01 Obsidian
story: Releasing as part of a sustainable line designed to lower the brand’s carbon footprint, the Nike Space Hippie 01 ‘Obsidian’ carries a navy blue knit upper made with ‘Space Waste Yarn,’ which includes recycled materials like T-shirts, fabric scraps and plastic water bottles. The sock-like build is mounted on a cream-hued Crater Foam midsole, which works in tandem with a plush sockliner constructed from ZoomX foam scraps — the same cushioning technology used on Nike’s pinnacle NEXT% running shoes.

name: Alpha Huarache 3 TF GS 'Light Smoke Grey Black'
Reebok Freestyle Hi Power Rangers Pink Ranger (W)
story: Releasing as part of a larger collection inspired by the ‘90s superhero franchise, the Power Rangers x Reebok women’s Freestyle High ‘Pterodactyl Zord’ gives the nod to the Pink Ranger’s battle vehicle. The high-top trainer utilizes a pink leather upper with white side stripes and a metallic silver heel overlay. ‘Pterodactyl’ is printed on the top ankle strap on the left shoe, while the left features text that reads ‘It’s Morphin Time.’ Underneath the straps, mismatched tongue tags reveal the Power Rangers’ lightning bolt logo and a pterodactyl graphic.

name: Wmns Waffle Racer Crater 'Yellow Strike Roma Green'
Wmns Zoom Air Fire 'White Light Lemon Twist'
Wmns Air Max 270 'Pink Oxford Metallic Silver'
Alpha Huarache Varsity 3 Turf 'Black Iron Grey'
Reebok Zig Dynamica Power Rangers Red Ranger (PS)
Marvel x Stan Smith Infant 'Hulk Smash'
Reebok Zig Kinetica II Power Rangers Red Ranger
story: Launching as part of a larger collection celebrating the television superhero series from the ‘90s, the Power Rangers x Reebok Zig Kinetica 2 ‘Dinozord’ takes inspiration from the battle craft piloted by the Red Ranger. The training shoe makes use of a crimson textile upper with a forefoot overlay ringed in a silver dinosaur tooth detailing. Mismatched tongue tags display the Power Rangers’ yellow lightning bolt and an illustrated Tyrannosaurus graphic. In terms of performance, the lightweight build is mounted on a responsive Floatride Fuel midsole with sidewalls arranged in a dynamic zigzag configuration.

name: Alpha Huarache Elite 3 Low 'Light Smoke Grey Royal'
Alpha Huarache Elite 3 Low 'Team Orange Black'
Wmns ZoomX Invincible Run Flyknit 'White Black'
Wmns Air Zoom Pegasus 38 'Iris Whisper Provence Purple'
Alpha Huarache Varsity 3 Turf 'Light Smoke Grey'
Nike Air Force 1 Low Acorn (2021)
story: The 2021 edition of the Nike Air Force 1 Low ‘Acorn’ brings back a popular earth-toned colorway of the classic hoops silhouette. The upper combines light tan canvas with leather overlays in a subtle beige finish. The same hue is repeated on the Swoosh and Nike branded woven tongue tag. A standard AF1 cupsole anchors the low-top, complete with encapsulated Nike Air cushioning in the heel. Underfoot, the brown rubber outsole features a traction pattern made for pivoting on the hardwood.

name: Racer TR21 J 'Crew Navy Solar Gold'
Wmns Venture Runner 'Light Bone Magic Ember'
Reebok Club C Power Rangers Yellow
story: The Power Rangers x Reebok Club C ‘Saber-Toothed Tiger Zord’ is taken from a nostalgic capsule collection celebrating the ‘90s television series. This pair draws inspiration from the Yellow Ranger’s battle craft, featuring a yellow leather upper marked with colorful graphics lifted directly from the Zord. Its fangs are represented by the sneaker’s metallic silver heel tab. Mismatched tongue tags feature a Saber-Toothed Tiger graphic and the Power Rangers’ lightning bolt logo.

name: Alpha Huarache Elite 3 Turf 'Light Smoke Grey Black'
Nike Dunk High Game Royal
story: Recalling the 1985 Be True to Your School 'Kentucky' colorway, the Dunk High 'Kentucky' released in June 2021. Built entirely with leather, the shoe's upper appears in a mix of white and Game Royal, with perforations on the toe box providing breathability. A nylon tongue is included for further breathability, while underfoot, the two-tone look continues onto the tooling, which includes an outsole with a concentric traction pattern.

name: Reebok Club C Legacy Power Rangers Blue Ranger
story: Taken from a larger collection celebrating the ‘90s superhero franchise, the Power Rangers x Reebok Club C ‘Triceratops Zord’ gives the nod to the Blue Ranger’s battle vehicle. The retro silhouette carries a royal blue leather upper with metallic silver detailing that represents the Zord’s horns. On each tongue, mismatched branding takes the form of a Triceratops graphic and the Power Rangers’ yellow lightning bolt logo. ‘It’s Morphin Time’ is inscribed in red text on the medial quarter panel, while the opposite side displays a Triceratops wordmark.

name: Reebok Question Mid Power Rangers Megazord
story: Launching as part of a limited collection celebrating the long-running superhero franchise, the Power Rangers x Reebok Question Mid 'Megazord Battle Mode!' transforms Allen Iverson’s debut signature shoe with an eclectic design inspired by the Dino Megazord. The synthetic leather upper features a black base with metallic silver overlays and mismatched toe caps in yellow and royal blue. Unique details include a debossed filigree design on the collar, printed silver eyelets that replicate the Zord’s teeth, and a Dinozord emblem on the back heel.

name: Reebok Freestyle Hi Power Rangers Pink Ranger (PS)
Wmns Flex Run 2021 'Iris Whisper'
colorway: Iris Whisper/Purple Pulse/Lime Ice/Deep Royal Blue

name: Reebok Nano X1 Power Rangers Black Ranger
story: Dropping as part of a limited collection with the colorful superhero franchise, the Power Rangers x Reebok Nano X1 ‘Coal’ dresses the performance training shoe in a black Flexweave knit upper. A gold emblem on the right tongue is accompanied by ‘Power Reeboks’ branding, while the Power Rangers’ lightning bolt logo graces the left tongue. In a nod to the ‘90s Black Ranger, the sleek silhouette features a metallic silver heel clip with subtle yellow and red accents. Floatride Energy Foam cushioning delivers a smooth ride.

name: Alpha Huarache Elite 3 Low 'Light Smoke Grey'
colorway: Light Smoke Grey/Iron Grey/Metallic Dark Grey/Black

name: Mercurial Superfly 8 Club CR7 MG 'Chile Red'
Slow Tides x All Coast Slide 'White Navy'
story: Designed in collaboration with the purveyors of artistic beach towels, the Slowtide x New Balance All Coast Slide ‘White Navy’ gives the lightweight sandal a clean two-tone makeover. Dual NB and Slowtide branding decorates the white bandage strap upper, featuring contrasting navy stitching and a textile-lined interior. A navy-colored contoured footbed yields step-in comfort, while a crisp white EVA midsole delivers soft cushioning with each step.

Mercurial Superfly 8 Academy CR7 MG 'Chile Red'

adidas Climacool Vento Crew Navy White
story: The adidas Climacool Vento ‘Crew Navy’ combines a ventilated build with responsive cushioning. Recycled content is incorporated into the dark blue upper, crafted from highly breathable mesh with tonal synthetic overlays for lightweight support. Floating white three-stripes adorn the quarter panel, while an orange tongue tag displays Climacool branding. Responsive cushioning arrives via a segmented Boost midsole, which works in tandem with a vented rubber outsole to improve airflow and dissipate interior heat.

name: Sunray Protect 2 TD 'Light Violet Crimson Bliss'
adidas Climacool Vento White Team Victory Red
story: The adidas Climacool Vento ‘White Team Victory Red’ presents a simplistic two-tone colorway of a running shoe designed to keep active feet from overheating. The seamless upper is constructed from ultra-breathable mesh in Cloud White. Tonal synthetic overlays provide lightweight support, while a molded heel counter offers rearfoot stability. Crimson accents make their way to floating three-stripes and a plaid textile interior lining. A segmented Boost midsole and vented rubber outsole allow air to circulate.

name: adidas Forum Mid S.E.E.D. (W)
story: The S.E.E.D. x adidas women’s Forum Mid ‘Multi’ is taken from a larger collection designed by the inaugural all-female class from the School for Experiential Education in Design. A discordant blend of colors is applied to mixed-material upper, highlighted by a mustard yellow leather toe box, pink leather quarter panel, and the Forum’s X-shaped overlay in pebbled brown leather. Bright aqua accents land on the sneaker’s adjustable ankle strap and webbing three-stripes. The vintage silhouette is mounted on a rubber cupsole, featuring contrast red stitching and a matching red rubber outsole.

name: adidas Climacool Vento Black Silver Metallic
Karlie Kloss x Wmns X9000 'Ambient Blush Multi'
END. x Neighborhood x Samba 'Black Leopard'
Saucony Azura Acribik Tech Noir
story: Conceived in partnership with the German sneaker boutique, the Acribik x Saucony Azura ‘Tech Noir’ draws inspiration from the movies and TV shows of the ‘80s. To that end, a gradient blend of purple and blue is executed on the synthetic leather forefoot overlay and lightweight EVA midsole. The rest of the of upper is crafted from black and white textile on the quarter panel and toe box, along with a black suede heel overlay marked with dual Saucony and Acribik branding.

name: adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate (Infant)
story: The adidas Yeezy 450 Infants ‘Dark Slate’ treats Kanye West’s futuristic silhouette to a stealthy finish. This scaled-down version for little feet makes use of a charcoal grey knit upper, accented with a subtle brownish tone along the heel. Lace-up closure combines with an elastic cuff to provide a snug, comfortable fit. The sneaker rides on a solid black EVA midsole, highlighted by tapered ‘fingers’ that wrap up the side panels. Exterior branding is limited to an adidas logo hit on the wavy outsole.

name: The Simpsons x Adilette Comfort Slides 'Bart'
Reebok Classic Leather Bronze 56K
story: Conceived in collaboration with the New York-based skate brand, the Bronze 56K x Reebok Classic Leather ‘New York Knicks’ features a familiar color scheme inspired by New York’s storied NBA franchise. The retro silhouette makes use of a bright blue nylon upper with white suede overlays and orange leather side stripes. Alongside a throwback Union Jack emblem, ‘Bronze’ is printed on the lateral-side logo window. Additional Bronze 56K branding lands on the sockliner and woven tongue tag. The sneaker rides on a full-length EVA midsole.

name: Nike Dunk High Sail Crimson Tint (W)
story: The Nike women’s Dunk High ‘Crimson Tint’ showcases a delicate palette that adheres to the traditional color blocking established with the debut ‘Be True to Your School’ series from 1985. The high-top is clad in white leather with contrasting overlays in a creamy pink hue. Traditional Nike branding decorates the sockliner and the woven tag stitched onto the nylon tongue. The two-tone dynamic is repeated on the sneaker’s tooling, featuring white sidewalls and a pastel-hued rubber outsole originally designed to grip the hardwood.

name: Yeezy 450 'Dark Slate'
story: The adidas Yeezy 450 ‘Dark Slate’ delivers a blacked-out iteration of Kanye West’s boundary-pushing silhouette. Stripped of color and exterior branding, the knit upper is secured with an integrated lacing system and topped with an elastic, sock-like cuff. In lieu of a traditional midsole, the rubber outsole sprouts tapered appendages that wrap up the heel and side panels of the deconstructed build, providing support and enhanced durability within its grasp.

name: Reebok Classic Leather Tabi Maison Margiela Project 0 Natural Beige
adidas Yeezy 450 Dark Slate (Kids)
story: The adidas Yeezy 450 Kids ‘Dark Slate’ updates Kanye West’s avant-garde design with a subdued, murky finish. A charcoal grey finish is applied to the heavyweight knit upper, featuring a subtle hit of brown on the heel. Rope laces and an elastic sock-like cuff combine for a secure fit. The sneaker’s defining feature is a black EVA midsole with a cage-like structure that gives the shoe its unique look. The wavy outsole is marked with an adidas logo under the toe.

name: Reebok Club C TL Maison Margiela Project 0 Natural Beige
Nike SB Dunk High Color Skates Kebab and Destroy
story: Crafted in partnership with the Athens-based skate shop, the Color Skates x Nike Dunk High SB ‘Kebab and Destroy’ takes inspiration from a mainstay of Greek cuisine: the gyro. The tan suede upper represents the pita wrap, the white leather toe box symbolizes tzatziki sauce, and the brown elephant-print heel overlay gives the nod to the protein component. Tomato-red accents land on the laces and leather Swoosh. Color Skates’ logo adorns the lateral heel of the left shoe, while the right features an embroidered gyro graphic. The same artwork is repeated on the custom insole, featuring Zoom Air cushioning in the heel and accompanying ‘All In’ text on the left shoe. ‘Kebab and Destroy’ is printed on the interior tongue tag.

name: Reebok Answer IV Bronze 56K
story: Crafted in partnership with the New York-based skate brand, the Bronze 56K x Reebok Answer 4 ‘Only The Strong Survive’ dresses Allen Iverson’s signature shoe with a soft white leather upper. Embroidered blue dice graphics enliven the zippered shroud, while dual Reebok and Bronze branding adorns the tongue. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a DMX foam midsole. Underfoot, the gum rubber outsole is stabilized with a TPU midfoot shank and inscribed with text that reads ‘Only the Strong Survive.’

name: Nike Air Force 1 Flyleather Mayumi Yamase White
story: The Mayumi Yamase x Nike Air Force 1 Flyleather ‘Earth Day’ delivers the Tokyo-based artist’s sustainable take on the sneaker icon. Inspired by her local green space (Yoyogi Park in Shibuya), Yamase applies mismatched accents that convey the feeling of natural elements. They take the form of hand-painted Swooshes and abstract figures, rendered in bright hues that add energy to an upper built with 50% recycled leather fiber. A translucent rubber cupsole packs a foam wedge and an Air-sole heel unit for lightweight cushioning.

name: adidas Superstar Kith Classics Program White
Kith x Gazelle 'Classics Program'
story: Taken from a heritage collection composed of six staple silhouettes, the Kith x adidas Gazelle ‘Classics Program’ delivers a minimalist take on the retro low-top. Premium white leather is utilized on the upper, accented with tonal pigskin suede on the toe overlay and signature three-stripes. A navy leather heel tab features Kith branding on the left shoe and an adidas Trefoil on the right, while ‘Kith Classics’ is stamped in gold foil lettering on the lateral quarter panel. The sneaker is mounted on a vintage off-white rubber cupsole.

name: Kith x Country 'Classics Program'
story: Launching as part of a minimalist six-piece collection, the Kith x adidas Country ‘Classics Program’ carries a premium white leather upper with tonal pigskin suede three-stripes. ‘Kith Classics’ is stamped in gold foil lettering on the lateral quarter panel. Contrasting navy blue accents settle on the printed tongue tag and heel tab, featuring a Kith logo on the left shoe and an adidas Trefoil on the right. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a two-tone foam midsole, reinforced underfoot by a tacky gum rubber outsole.

name: Lauren London x Wmns Suede 'Forever Stronger'
story: The Lauren London x PUMA women’s Suede ‘Forever Stronger’ is taken from a larger capsule collection inspired by the actress’ hometown of Los Angeles. The vintage silhouette is clad in soft black suede with a contrasting white embroidered Formstrip. Dual PUMA and Lauren London branding adorns the woven tongue tag and sockliner, while ‘Forever Stronger’ is stamped on the lateral heel. A durable off-white rubber cupsole anchors the low-top.

name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Ken Griffey Jr. and Sr. Swingman
adidas Samba OG Kith Classics Program White
Fresh Foam X LAV v2 4E Wide 'White Laser Blue'
Racer TR21 Infant 'Crew Navy Solar Gold'
Kith x Samba OG 'Classics Program'
story: Releasing as part of a minimalist six-piece collection with the New York-based retailer, the Kith x adidas Samba OG ‘Classics Program’ features a white leather upper with tonal suede detailing on the T-toe overlay and signature three-stripes. Mismatched Kith and adidas Trefoil branding adorns the green leather heel tab of each shoe, while ‘Kith Classics’ is inscribed in metallic gold on the lateral quarter panel. The streamlined silhouette rests on a standard gum rubber cupsole.

name: Air Griffey Max 1 GS 'Sweetest Swing'
story: Made for big kids, the Nike Air Griffey Max 1 GS ‘Sweetest Swing’ brings back Ken Griffey Jr.’s signature shoe on the occasion of its 25th anniversary. The retro trainer gets dressed in a familiar palette inspired by the original ‘Freshwater’ colorway, featuring a white leather upper with an adjustable ankle strap and a metallic gold Swoosh. Junior’s Swingman logo adorns the black leather heel overlay, featuring red baseball-style stitching and a tonal wood grain print. The heel is further embellished with Junior’s Swingman logo. The mid-top rides on a teal-colored midsole with visible Max Air cushioning under the forefoot and heel.

name: Air Griffey Max 1 PS 'Sweetest Swing'
story: Built for little kids, the Nike Air Griffey Max 1 PS ‘Sweetest Swing’ brings back Ken Griffey Jr.’s signature shoe in a familiar palette that recalls the OG ‘Freshwater’ colorway. Rope laces and an adjustable ankle strap combine to secure the white leather upper, fortified with a black leather mudguard and accented with a metallic gold Swoosh. Red baseball-style stitching surrounds the heel overlay, which is marked with the Kid’s embroidered Swingman logo. The mid-top is mounted on a teal-colored midsole with red-tinged Max Air cushioning.

name: Puma Future Rider White Castle
story: Celebrating the fast foot chain’s century in business, the White Castle x PUMA Future Rider ‘100th Anniversary’ features a unique design inspired by the eatery’s signature square sliders. The upper is crafted from white textile with blue nylon paneling and a tonal leather Formstrip. White Castle branding adorns the exposed foam tongue, while a yellow ‘5¢’ tab is affixed to the sneaker’s lateral side. Mismatched graphics on each heel overlay is accompanied by text that reads ‘Buy ‘em by the sack’ and ‘A legend in a bun.’ Underfoot, PUMA’s Federbein outsole is rendered in a royal blue finish.

name: adidas Campus 80s Kith Classics Program White
Puma Suede White Castle
story: The White Castle x PUMA Suede ‘100th Anniversary’ celebrates the fast food chain’s century in business. The vintage low-top draws inspiration from White Castle’s signature sliders, featuring a white suede upper with a blue leather Formstrip. Five circles on the heel tab give the nod to the sliders’ distinctive beef patties. White Castle’s logo adorns the right tongue, while PUMA branding decorates the left. Underfoot, the translucent rubber outsole features ‘Crave’ and ‘100 Years’ inscribed across the left and right shoe.

name: adidas Golf Adilette Boost Slide Extra Butter Happy Gilmore
story: The Extra Butter x Happy Gilmore x adidas Adilette Boost Slide ‘Happy’ celebrates the 25th anniversary of Adam Sandler’s hit comedy film, centered around a failed hockey player turned reluctant golf pro. New York sneaker boutique Extra Butter dresses the sandal in a lush green synthetic leather upper, accented with white three-stripes and ‘Happy Gilmore 25th Anniversary’ inscribed on the lateral side. Dual adidas and Extra Butter branding adorns the matching green footbed, which sits atop a full-length Boost midsole.

name: Nike Dunk Low Free 99 White
story: Dropping as part of the ‘Free.99’ pack, the Nike Dunk Low SE ‘White’ features mismatched color blocking between the left and right shoe. The jumbled hues — spanning a discordant mix of red, green, yellow and powder blue — are contrasted by a white leather base, a matching white textile tongue and a brown leather Swoosh. Inside the shoe, the custom sockliner displays ‘Free .99’ price stickers. Both shoes are supported by a clean white midsole and peach-colored rubber outsole.

name: adidas ZG21 Spiked Golf Extra Butter Chubbs Happy Gilmore
story: The Extra Butter x Happy Gilmore x adidas ZG21 Spiked ‘Chubbs’ is taken from a capsule collection celebrating the 25th anniversary of Adam Sandler’s comedy film about a frustrated hockey player turned professional golfer. Featuring a neutral palette, this performance golf cleat pays tribute to Chubbs Peterson, Happy’s one-handed mentor. The cream white leather upper features brogue detailing and faux gator quarter panels in a nod to the creature that took Chubbs’ right hand. Fringed kiltie overlays feature mismatched adidas and Extra Butter branding. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of an EVA midsole with a Boost drop-in under the heel.

name: adidas Gazelle Kith Classics Program White
Reebok Question Mid Draft Night 25th Anniversary
story: The Reebok Question Mid ‘Draft Night’ showcases an eclectic palette celebrating the 25th anniversary of the legendary 1996 NBA draft, where Allen Iverson was selected first overall by the Philadelphia 76ers. In a nod to AI’s draft day suit, the sneaker wears a neutral grey suede upper, contrasted by a teal-colored collar lining and royal blue and red accents inspired by the 76ers. Lightweight cushioning arrives via an EVA midsole, featuring Hexalite cushioning and interchangeable heel patches for a custom look.

name: Kith x Campus 80s 'Classics Program'
story: The Kith x adidas Campus 80s ‘Classics Program’ is drawn from a heritage collection made up of six essential silhouettes. Like its companion colorways, this pair utilizes a premium white leather upper with tonal suede three-stripes and gold foil Kith Classics branding. Green leather heel tabs are embellished with a Kith logo on the left shoe and an adidas Trefoil on the right. Underfoot, the off-white rubber cupsole features a herringbone traction pattern for optimal grip.

name: New Balance 2002R Salehe Bembury Water Be The Guide
story: Developed in collaboration with the LA-based footwear designer, the Salehe Bembury x New Balance 2002R ‘Water Be The Guide’ takes inspiration from the universal solvent. The upper is constructed from open pink mesh with shaggy suede overlays in a vibrant aqua hue. Contrasting green hits appear on the heel and shearling ‘N’ logo, while rustic brown leather is utilized on the tongue and collar. Soft cushioning is provided by a speckled NERGY foam midsole with a Stability Web TPU shank for improved stability.

name: Fresh Foam X LAV v2 2E Wide 'White Laser Blue'
Nike Air VaporMax Plus Griffey Swingman
story: The Ken Griffey Jr. x Nike Air VaporMax Plus ‘Spider-Man Catch’ features an insole graphic that displays a ’24’ ensnared in a teal-colored spider web. The former refers to Ken Griffey Jr.’s jersey number, while the latter is symbolic of Junior’s iconic web gem from 1991. Up top, the Air Max Plus-inspired design combines a white mesh base with black TPU overlays, exposed red stitching and a pull tab in Fresh Water — a color combination that nods to the Kid’s OG signature shoe. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of Nike’s full-length VaporMax unit.

name: Nike LeBron 8 V2 Sprite (2021)
story: The 2021 edition of the Nike LeBron 8 V/2 Low ‘Sprite’ brings back the lively colorway a decade after its original release. Unofficially named after the soda brand endorsed by LeBron James, the sneaker rides on a buoyant Max Air 360 unit in Volt green. The neon hue is repeated on the rubber outsole, collar lining and upper eyelets. The synthetic upper is rendered in a bold Treasure Blue finish, featuring embedded Flywire support and a contrasting white Swoosh that ends on a spoiler-like heel loop.

name: adidas Ultra Boost 1.0 Extra Butter Shooter Happy Gilmore
story: The Happy Gilmore x Extra Butter x adidas UltraBoost 1.0 ‘Gold Jacket’ celebrates the 25th anniversary of Adam Sandler’s hit comedy film, centered around a failed hockey player turned professional golfer. The New York-based retailer dresses the lifestyle runner in yellow Primeknit — a nod to the coveted gold jacket awarded to Happy after he beats Shooter McGavin at the Tour Championship. The upper is reinforced with a white midfoot cage and tonal suede overlays at the heel and forefoot, the latter imprinted with a graphic depicting Shooter’s signature finger-gun gesture. Dual Extra Butter and adidas branding adorns the sockliner.

name: Nike Dunk SB High Pro Ishod Wair x Magnus Walker
story: Pro skater Ishod Wair enlisted the help of designer Magnus Walker, a fellow LA car enthusiast, to develop the Nike Dunk High Pro SB ‘Urban Outlaw.’ The name is borrowed from Walker’s renowned short film, featuring a custom Porsche 911 dressed in the same colors and graphics used on the shoe. They include a Union Jack emblem and assorted racing style visuals on a cracked white leather upper, featuring a wear-away outer layer that reveals a base layer of gold. Contrasting hits of color arrive via a blue leather Swoosh, red textile toe box, and mismatched red and blue tartan plaid on the collar lining of each shoe. A distressed finish is applied to the midsole, accented with Nike SB branding on the lateral sidewall and supported by a two-tone rubber outsole.

name: Nike Blazer Low 77 Flyleather Mayumi Yamase White
story: Crafted in partnership with the Tokyo-based artist, the Mayumi Yamase x Nike Blazer Low ‘77 Flyleather ‘Earth Day’ features a sustainable build, composed of 50% recycled leather fiber and synthetic materials. Mismatched, multicolored accents are both printed and embroidered on a stark white upper, enhancing the shoe’s handcrafted aesthetic. Atop the exposed foam tongue, a woven tag displays a green painted Swoosh, while ‘Nike’ is embroidered on the textile heel tab in orange lettering that replicates a hand-scrawled look. Underfoot, a gum rubber outsole features a herringbone traction pattern for optimal grip.

name: Kith x Pro Model 'Classics Program'
story: Dropping as a part of a minimalist six-piece collection, the Kith x adidas Pro Model ‘Classics Program’ employs a premium white leather upper with tonal suede three-stripes. ‘Kith Classics’ in gold foil lettering replaces the traditional ‘Pro Model’ wordmark on the lateral side panel. Contrasting navy accents settle on the printed tongue tag and heel tab, which displays a Kith logo on the left shoe and an adidas Trefoil on the right. The shell-toed silhouette is mounted on an off-white rubber cupsole, featuring a herringbone traction pattern underfoot.

name: adidas Country Kith Classics Program White
Fresh Foam X LAV v2 'White Laser Blue'
adidas Pro Model 1970 Kith Classics Program White
Kith x Superstar 'Classics Program'
story: Releasing as part of a six-piece heritage collection, the Kith x adidas Superstar ‘Classics Program’ carries a white leather upper with tonal suede three-stripes and contrasting green heel tabs, accented with a Kith logo on the left shoe and an adidas Trefoil on the right. ‘Kith Classics’ in gold foil lettering replaces the traditional Superstar wordmark. The sneaker is mounted on a vintage off-white rubber cupsole, featuring a standard herringbone traction pattern underfoot.

name: Nike Dunk Low SE Easter Candy (W)
story: The Nike women’s Dunk Low SE ‘Candy’ updates the vintage basketball shoe with an eye-catching medley of colors. The low-tops showcases a unique color blocking, highlighted by a white leather base with mismatched accents — including Purple Pulse, Sunset Pulse, Lagoon Pulse and Green Glow — throughout the sneaker’s overlays, Swooshes, Nike-branded tongue tags and mesh collar linings. The rubber cupsole pairs white sidewalls with a speckled yellow outsole.

name: Nike Air Griffey Max 1 Swingman Sweetest Swing
Nike Dunk Low Free 99 White (GS)
story: Constructed for big kids, the Nike Dunk Low SE GS ‘Free.99’ showcases mismatched color blocking on an all-leather upper. Both the left and right shoe feature the same white leather base with a dark brown Swoosh, while the overlays, tongue tags and collar linings are rendered in a mixed medley of vibrant hues. Inside the shoe, a ‘Free.99’ graphic on the sockliner pays homage to neighborhood bodegas. Underfoot, a dull orange hue is applied to the rubber outsole.

name: Nike Dunk Low UNC (2021) (TD)
story: The Nike Dunk Low TD ‘University Blue’ treats the iconic silhouette to classic color blocking that recalls the original ‘Be True to Your School’ series from 1985. No-tie elastic laces secure the leather upper, featuring a crisp white base with contrasting overlays in a pastel blue finish. Step-in comfort is provided by a padded mesh collar and breathable nylon tongue, topped with a woven Nike tag for an OG touch. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a concentric-circle traction pattern for reliable grip.

name: STAUD x 57/40 'Agave Green'
story: Launching as part of a sunny capsule collection with the LA-based fashion brand, the STAUD x New Balance 57/40 ‘Agave Green’ treats the lifestyle runner to a pastel makeover. Varying bright green shades are executed on the upper, crafted from breathable mesh with suede overlays. An oversized ‘N’ logo in vivid yellow delivers a contrasting pop of color. Dual NB and STAUD branding decorates the sockliner and woven tongue tag. Lightweight cushioning is provided by an EVA midsole, supported underfoot by an off road-inspired rubber outsole.

name: 550 'White Navy'
story: The New Balance 550 ‘White Navy’ confers a simple two-tone palette to a vintage hoops shoe originally released in 1989. The layered white leather upper is contrasted by a series of navy blue accents, highlighted by a raised ‘N’ logo and ‘550’ inscribed on the lateral forefoot. Additional details include a breathable nylon tongue, padded textile collar and a suede forefoot overlay. The sneaker’s retro tooling comprises a sturdy rubber cupsole with an exposed EVA wedge on the medial sidewall.

name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Cinder
story: Launching as part of a four-piece ‘Mono’ pack, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Cinder’ applies a black-out finish to the lifestyle sneaker. The revised design features an upper crafted from monofilament mesh, reinforced with an interior cage and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. A webbing pull tab at the heel allows the sock-like build to be easily slipped on and off. The stealthy palette extends to the midsole, featuring wrapped Boost cushioning that runs the length of the rubber outsole. This shoe released exclusively on Yeezy Supply.

name: Reebok Kamikaze II Low NERF NERFOOP
story: Dropping as part of a larger capsule collection with the popular toy brand, the NERF x Reebok Kamikaze 2 Low ‘Backboard Breaker’ highlights vibrant hues on a retro hoops shoe made famous by the high-flying Shawn Kemp. The sneaker takes inspiration from NERF’s Big Bad Backboard from 1995, featuring a black synthetic nubuck upper with a magenta paint splatter effect and forefoot underlays in lime green. NERF branding settles on the tongue and heel, while ‘Maximum Attitude!’ is inscribed on the toe box. The low-top is mounted on a multicolor EVA midsole, supported by a translucent rubber outsole.

name: STAUD x 327 'Sea Salt Atlantic'
story: Releasing as part of a capsule collection with the LA-based fashion brand, the STAUD x New Balance 327 ‘Sea Salt Atlantic’ dresses the retro-inspired silhouette in ivory-colored textile with an oversized ‘N’ logo in powder blue. A darker shade of blue is applied to the heel overlay, featuring contrasting white stitching and ‘NB / STAUD’ debossed on the lateral side. The lightweight build is propped on a wedge-shaped EVA midsole, reinforced underfoot by a studded gum rubber outsole.

name: New Balance 550 White Purple
story: The New Balance 550 ‘White Purple’ delivers a simplistic two-tone colorway of the retro hoops shoe originally released in 1989. The upper is composed of white leather with a tonal suede forefoot overlay and contrasting violet accents throughout. They include a TPU heel clip, a raised ‘N’ logo on the quarter panel, and ‘550’ stamped on the lateral forefoot. The low-top rests on a durable rubber cupsole, featuring an exposed EVA wedge on the medial sidewall.

name: Daniel Moon x Classic Leather Legacy 'Solar Pink Pushy Purple'
story: The Daniel Moon x Reebok Classic Leather Legacy ‘Solar Pink Pushy Purple’ features a medley of vibrant hues assembled by the acclaimed hair colorist. The retro-inspired lifestyle runner makes use of a pink textile upper with blue leather side stripes and suede overlays in purple and orange. In a nod to Moon’s artistic medium, ‘Hair’ is inscribed on each tongue and a logo piece affixed to the right shoe. The sneaker rides on a pink die-cut EVA midsole, good for soft cushioning with each step.

name: Reebok Kamikaze II NERF NERFOOP
story: The NERF x Reebok Kamikaze 2 ‘Backboard Breaker’ is drawn from a nostalgic collection with the popular toy brand. Made famous by Shawn Kemp, the retro hoops shoe is updated with asymmetrical color blocking and a mismatched leather and nubuck paneling. ‘95’ is embroidered on the heel tab, nodding to the release year of both the sneaker and NERF’s Big Bad Backboard, the game on which the shoe’s design is based. In addition to a jumbled blend of magenta, lime green, orange, black, yellow, purple, and powder blue, the mid-top is appointed with paint splatter detailing at the heel and NERF branding on the tongue and lateral forefoot.

name: Puma Basket Vintage Butter Goods Corduroy
Air VaporMax 2021 Flyknit GS 'White Metallic Silver'
Hirocoledge x Adizero Adios 5 'Tokyo - Black White'
Daniel Moon x Club C Legacy 'Solar Green'
story: Designed in collaboration with the renowned hair colorist, the Daniel Moon x Reebok Club C Legacy ‘Solar Green’ updates the retro silhouette with refreshed materials and a fluorescent palette. The upper is crafted from bright green mesh with tonal overlays in leather and suede. The one-note finish is disrupted by pink contrast stitching and hits of black on the collar lining and a pair of webbing pull tabs. ‘Hair’ is inscribed on the tongue and a translucent logo piece on the right shoe. The low-top is mounted on a clear rubber cupsole, featuring drop-in EVA cushioning for a smooth ride.

name: Wmns Air VaporMax 2021 Flyknit 'White Pure Platinum'
Jordan 1 Low OG Neutral Grey (2021) (GS)
story: The 2021 reissue of the Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG GS ‘Neutral Grey’ brings back the original 1985 colorway in big kid sizing. Like the original, the vintage silhouette carries a pristine white leather upper with light grey suede on the signature Swoosh and heel tab, the latter embellished with a Jordan Wings logo. Nike Air branding makes its way to the sockliner and woven tongue tag. The low-top rides on a rubber cupsole with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning under the heel.

name: Nike Dunk Low UNC (2021) (GS)
story: Made for big kids, the Nike Dunk Low GS ‘University Blue’ features a leather upper in a color-blocked design redolent of the shoe’s collegiate hardwood roots. A crisp white base is contrasted by a pastel blue finish on the shoe’s eyestay, Swoosh, and heel and forefoot overlays. Classic Nike branding lands on the woven tongue tag and heel tag. The low-top sits on a durable rubber cupsole, underpinned by an outsole that features performance-ready traction.

name: Nike Dunk Low UNC (2021) (PS)
story: Crafted for little kids, the Nike Dunk Low PS ‘University Blue’ showcases a simple two-tone palette that recalls the silhouette’s 1985 debut as a college team shoe. The leather upper is rendered in a stark white finish with contrasting powder blue overlays. Nike branding lands on the heel tab, woven tongue tag and foam sockliner, which combines with a padded low-cut collar to deliver a comfortable fit. The low-top is underpinned by a durable rubber outsole originally designed to grip the hardwood.

name: Jordan 4 Retro SP 30th Anniversary Union Desert Moss
story: Releasing as part of the renowned retailer’s 30th anniversary festivities, the Union LA x Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Desert Moss’ brings back the creative partners’ modified AJ4 from 2020. This pair is taken from a capsule dubbed ‘Tent and Trail,’ featuring colors and materials inspired by outdoor gear from the ‘80s and ‘90s. The mid-top carries an upper built with a blend of bright purple mesh and mustard yellow suede. Vibrant pops of turquoise land on the lower molded eyelets and heel tab, marked with Nike Air branding in a lavender hue. A stitched fold-down tongue, yellow ‘UN/LA’ tag and translucent TPU wings are carried over from the 2020 release. The sneaker is mounted on an off-white polyurethane midsole with an aqua-tinged Air-sole unit under the heel.

name: Reebok Pump Omni Zone II NERF Light Jammer Black
story: Launching as part of a limited four-piece collection with the sports-themed toy brand, the NERF x Reebok Pump Omni Zone 2 ‘Backboard Breaker’ takes inspiration from the Nerfoop Big Bad Backboard from 1995. The retro hoops shoe makes use of a black synthetic nubuck upper with magenta paint splatter effects throughout the vamp and collar. Contrasting yellow accents highlight the TPU midfoot overlay and NERF branding hits at the lateral forefoot and tongue, the latter equipped with a bright blue rubber pump button.

name: Jordan 1 Low OG Neutral Grey (2021) (W)
story: The women's Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG ‘Neutral Grey’ brings back one of the original low-top colorways from 1985. The understated design combines a stark white leather upper with neutral grey accents on the suede Swoosh and heel tab, the latter embellished with an Air Jordan Wings logo. Nike Air branding lands on the insole and woven tongue tag. The low-profile silhouette is mounted on a classic rubber cupsole, featuring a foam wedge and encapsulated Air sole cushioning.

name: Nike Dunk Low UNC (2021)
story: The Nike Dunk Low ‘University Blue’ delivers a simplistic two-tone colorway of the retro silhouette, rendered in classic color blocking that recalls the sneaker’s OG slate of colorways from 1985. The all-leather upper is accented with powder blue overlays and a matching blue Swoosh. A traditional woven Nike tag adorns the lightly breathable nylon tongue, which combines with a padded collar for a comfortable fit. The low-top is mounted on a standard rubber cupsole.

name: Reebok Pump Omni Zone II NERF Light Jammer Orange
story: Launching as part of a nostalgic capsule with the popular toy brand, the Nerf x Reebok Pump Omni Zone II ‘Light Jammer’ gives the retro ‘90s hoops shoe a colorful makeover. Paint splatter effects are applied to the synthetic leather upper, rendered in vibrant Solar Orange and Solar Lime hues. Nerf logos on the Pump-buttoned tongue and lateral forefoot are joined by ‘Light Jammer’ branding, nodding to the classic Nerfoop light switch cover released in 1996. Underfoot, the full-length rubber outsole is treated to a glow-in-the-dark finish.

name: New Balance 550 White Green
story: The New Balance 550 ‘White Green’ showcases a throwback hardwood design lifted directly from the brand’s late ‘80s archives. White leather is utilized on the upper, featuring microperforated paneling and a tonal suede overlay that wraps around the toe. Forest green accents make their way to the sneaker’s various branding elements, including a raised ‘N’ logo and an oversized tongue tag marked with ‘New Balance 550.’ The low-profile silhouette sits on a rubber cupsole with soft EVA cushioning.

name: Hirocoledge x UltraBoost Summer.Rdy 'Tokyo - Black White'
adidas Campus Yara Shahidi
story: Taken from an apparel and footwear collection developed with the actress and activist, the Yara Shahidi x adidas Campus ‘Floral’ enlivens the gold textile upper with an intricate green and brown floral print that incorporates the adidas Trefoil. Additional details include gold suede three-stripes, embroidered eyelets and metallic gold lace jewels. ‘Yar,’ a play on Yara’s name meaning ‘friend,’ is embroidered in Persian lettering atop the right tongue. The low-profile silhouette rides on an off-white rubber cupsole.

Wmns Fresh Foam Roav Wide 'Moon Dust Leopard'

Nike ACG Air Deschutz Sig Zane
adidas Boston Super X Marathon Yara Shahidi
story: Launching as part of a larger collection with the actress and activist, the Yara Shahidi x adidas Boston Super Marathon ‘Forest Night Yellow’ debuts a hybrid silhouette that blends details from two classic runners, the Boston Super and Marathon. A dark green hue is executed on the upper, crafted from textile with tonal suede overlays and contrasting yellow leather three-stripes. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features high-traction lugs in the shape of adidas Trefoils.

name: Nike Dunk Low Retro PRM Animal Pack Giraffe/Cheetah
story: Releasing as one-half of the two-piece ‘Animal Pack,’ the Nike Dunk Low Premium ‘Cheetah’ updates the vintage silhouette with a cream-colored leather upper. Tonal suede overlays are embellished with a subtle cheetah print, while contrasting brown accents make their way to the collar lining, leather Swoosh and heel tab, featuring an embroidered Nike wordmark. Additional Nike branding lands on the sockliner and a woven tag stitched atop a lightly padded nylon tongue.

name: Classic Leather Legacy AZ 'Stucco Silver Metallic'
Wmns Air Zoom Terra Kiger 7 'Light Soft Pink Magic Ember'
Natasha Cloud x Wmns Run Star Hike Inspired 'Floral - Pink Quartz'
Wmns Adilette Lite Slide 'Pink Tint'
story: The adidas women’s Adilette Lite Slide ‘Pink Tint’ applies a subdued, pastel finish to a slip-on sandal built for all-day comfort. Synthetic leather is employed on the wide bandage-strap upper, featuring an oversized Trefoil logo in white. A soft textile lining, contoured footbed and EVA midsole all combine to deliver a smooth ride. The outsole is equipped with a diamond traction pattern that yields reliable traction on wet or dry surfaces.

name: Wmns Gel Cumulus 23 'Smokey Rose Deep Mars'
Air Jordan 1 Mid PS 'Tropical Twist'
story: Built for little kids, the Air Jordan 1 Mid PS ‘Tropical Twist’ highlights pastel accents on a classic silhouette inspired by Peter Moore’s original high-top design from 1985. The all-leather upper combines a crisp white base with a black forefoot overlay and bright turquoise hits on the Swoosh, heel overlay and collar flap, featuring Jordan Wings branding stamped in black on the lateral side. A rubber cupsole anchors the mid-top, underpinned by a grippy traction pattern tested by time.

name: Gel Cumulus 23 'Black Glow Yellow'
story: The ASICS Gel Cumulus 23 ‘Black Glow Yellow’ features outlined tiger stripes on a lightweight runner named after fluffy cumulus clouds. Recycled content is incorporated into the black engineered mesh upper, designed to wrap around the foot with targeted areas of enhanced support or breathability. The lightweight build is mounted on a crisp white FlyteFoam midsole, with Gel cushioning in the heel for superior impact protection. A bright yellow rubber outsole provides durable traction.

name: Jordan 1 Mid Tropical Twist Igloo
story: The Air Jordan 1 Mid ‘Tropical Twist’ injects a vibrant burst of color to a classic silhouette modeled after Peter Moore’s original high-top from 1985. The all-leather upper features a crisp white base with a contrasting black forefoot overlay and bright teal accents on the Swoosh, eyestay, heel overlay and collar flap, imprinted with a black Wings logo on the lateral side. Jumpman branding decorates the woven tongue tag. The mid-top rides on a rubber cupsole with encapsulated Nike Air cushioning in the heel.

name: Wmns Fresh Foam 680v7 'Silver Thunder'
story: The New Balance women’s Fresh Foam 680v7 ‘Silver Thunder’ delivers cushioned comfort for beginner and casual runners. Grey engineered mesh makes up the composition of the upper, accented with a matching grey ‘N’ logo outlined in pink. A padded low-cut collar offers a comfortable fit, while a tonal no-sew overlay wraps around the toe for added durability. The streamlined build rests on a wedge-shaped Fresh Foam midsole, supported underfoot by a pink and yellow rubber outsole.

name: Wmns 992 Made In USA Wide 'Cork'
story: The New Balance women’s 992 Made In USA Wide ‘Cork’ delivers a neutral colorway of the running shoe originally released in 2006, coinciding with the 100th anniversary of the Boston brand. The upper combines recycled polyester Spinnex material with suede overlays in a muted beige hue. Reflective silver overlays are joined by genuine cork accents and brown leather detailing at the heel tab and tongue. Lightweight cushioning is provided by an ENCAP midsole with ABZORB SBS cushioning under the heel.

name: Wmns Jordan MA2 'Light Bone Sunset Pulse'
story: The women’s Jordan MA2 ‘Light Bone Sunset Pulse’ adds vibrant accents to an otherwise neutral colorway of the lifestyle silhouette. The upper combines ivory mesh with tonal suede overlays and a translucent pink pull loop affixed to the lateral collar. A darker shade of pink is applied to a textured rubber kick plate at the heel, which allows wearers to kick off their shoes without using their hands. A final hit of contrasting color makes its way to the Max Air 200 unit under the heel.

name: Wmns Floatride Energy Daily 'White Mint Acid Yellow'
Wmns Fresh Foam 680v7 2E Wide 'Silver Thunder'
story: The New Balance women’s Fresh Foam 680v7 2E Wide ‘Silver Thunder’ provides a cushy ride for casual runners. The seamless upper is crafted from grey engineered mesh with subtle pink accents and signature ‘N’ branding on the quarter panel. A molded sockliner works in tandem with a Fresh Foam midsole to deliver lightweight cushioning with every step. Underfoot, the durable rubber outsole offers grippy traction and additional pops of color.

name: Adilette Lite Slide J 'Pastel Dreamy Swirls'
story: Offered in kids sizing, the adidas Adilette Lite Slide J ‘Pastel Dreamy Swirls’ updates the slip-on sandal with a medley of soft colors throughout the bandage strap upper, made with synthetic leather and branded with a large adidas Trefoil. A contoured footbed gives way to a pink EVA midsole with an embossed adidas wordmark on the lateral sidewall. Underfoot, the outsole features a diamond traction pattern for grippy traction.

name: Nike Dunk Low Retro Animal Pack Zebra
story: Launching as part of the two-piece ‘Animal Pack,’ the Nike Dunk Low Premium ‘Zebra’ carries a black leather upper with tonal suede overlays covered in subtle zebra stripes. The dark palette is offset by a white leather Swoosh and a matching white heel tab with embroidered Nike branding. Padded mesh lines the collar for a comfortable fit, while a nylon tongue offers improved breathability. The sneaker rests on a solid white rubber cupsole, underpinned by a traction pattern originally designed for pivoting on the hardwood.

name: Wmns Electrify Nitro 'Nimbus Cloud Blue Fog'
Wmns Fresh Foam 680v7 Wide 'Silver Thunder'
story: The New Balance women’s Fresh Foam 680v7 Wide ‘Silver Thunder’ presents a running shoe that mingles a seamless build with an ultra-cushioned ride. The latter is made possible by a wedge-shaped Fresh Foam midsole, engineered to deliver lightweight cushioning and a smooth transition. Up top, grey engineered mesh is accented with subtle pink accents and a prominent ‘N’ logo on the quarter panel. All-day comfort comes courtesy of a low-cut padded collar and breathable mesh tongue.

adidas Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange (Infants)
story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Infant ‘Enflame Orange’ dresses the minimalist slip-on in a bold citrus hue. The lightweight sandal is crafted from injected EVA foam and features a soft footbed marked with adidas’ three stripes logo, representing the only instance of exterior branding. An adjustable strap wraps around the heel for an extra-secure fit. Underfoot, a series of deep grooves are carved into the outsole, delivering a blend of impact protection and grippy traction.

name: Wmns Nergize Sport Wide 'Sea Salt Garnet'
Nike Air Force 1 Low Daktari
story: The Nike Air Force 1 Low Premium ‘Daktari Stripes’ takes direct inspiration from a duo of ‘Daktari’ Dunk Low colorways from 2003. The upper combines a leather base in Coconut Milk with zebra-print suede overlays in Atomic Orange. Additional orange accents settle on the Swoosh and Nike branding hits atop the brown leather heel tab and matching brown tongue tag. Underfoot, the AF1’s signature pivot-point outsole is rendered in grippy gum rubber.

adidas Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange (Kids)
story: The adidas Yeezy Slide Kids ‘Enflame Orange’ delivers a vibrant colorway of Kanye West’s futuristic sandal. A monochromatic citrus finish is executed on a slip-on built with lightweight and durable EVA foam. adidas’ Three Stripes logo is embossed on the footbed, featuring a soft surface for step-in comfort. The outsole is equipped with an aggressive ripple tread, good for both improved cushioning and superior grip.

name: adidas Yeezy Slide Enflame Orange
story: The adidas Yeezy Slide ‘Enflame Orange’ updates the minimalist slip-on with a deep citrus hue. The lightweight build, formed with injected EVA, features breathable open-toe construction and a plush footbed for soft landings. The latter is marked with adidas’ three-stripe logo, representing the only bit of exterior branding. Pronounced flex grooves distinguish the outsole, offering improved cushioning and durable traction.

Nike LeBron 8 V2 Low Miami Nights (2021)
story: The 2021 edition of the Nike LeBron 8 V/2 Low Retro ‘Miami Night’ brings back a popular colorway originally released in 2011, coinciding with LeBron James’ first season with the Miami Heat. Inspired by South Beach’s bright neon lights, the Flywire-infused textile upper is tinged in turquoise and coral hues and enlivened with black speckled detailing. The Swoosh is moved back and extends to a spoiler-like loop at the heel, which reveals LeBron’s signature and an embossed mini-Swoosh. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a compression-molded Phylon midsole and a full-length Max Air unit in Solar Red.

name: Air Jordan 1 Mid TD 'Crimson Tint'
story: The Air Jordan 1 Mid TD ‘Arctic Orange’ adds fresh colors to a condensed build made for little feet. An added pull tab at the heel provides easy entry into the upper, crafted from white leather with a contrasting black toe and matching black nylon tongue. Subtle pink accents appear on the Swoosh, heel overlay and collar flap, marked with a Wings logo on the lateral side. Underfoot, a solid rubber outsole is equipped with deep flex grooves and a circular traction pattern.

name: Dunk Low N7 By You
story: The Nike Dunk Low N7 By You is drawn from the N7 Summer 2021 collection, featuring footwear and apparel rooted in the artistic traditions of Native American and Indigenous communities in North America. The Nike Dunk Low N7 By You is highlighted by optional braided detailing around the Swoosh and heel tab, as well as decorative embroidery throughout the upper. Atop the tongue, a leather Nike tag gives way to an extended lace guard stamped with an N7 logo. Additional N7 branding lands on the sockliner. A standard rubber cupsole anchors the low-top.

name: Wmns Crater Remixa 'Grey Fog Chambray Blue'
Air Jordan 1 Mid PS 'Crimson Tint'
story: Constructed for little kids, the Air Jordan 1 Mid PS ‘Arctic Orange’ utilizes a traditional leather build with an added webbing pull tab at the heel for easy on and off. The upper combines a stark white base with contrasting-colored overlays: black along the forefoot, and soft pink around the heel and collar. Additional pastel accents make their way to the leather Swoosh, Jumpman-branded tongue tag and durable rubber outsole, featuring a concentric-circle traction pattern originally designed for the hardwood.

name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Leopard
story: The Nike Air Force 1 Low Premium ‘Snow Leopard’ treats the iconic silhouette to a subtle animal-print makeover. The sneaker makes use of a leather build in Pure Platinum, fortified with tonal suede overlays covered in grey leopard spots. A leather Swoosh in Light Blue Fury delivers a contrasting pop of color. The vibrant hue is repeated on the Nike branding that adorns the black leather heel tab and tongue tag. Lightweight cushioning arrives via an Air-infused foam midsole, wrapped in white rubber and supported underfoot by a translucent outsole.

name: Wmns Nergize Sport Wide 'Garnet Pink Glow'

Jordan 4 Retro SP 30th Anniversary Union Taupe Haze
story: The Union LA x Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Taupe Haze’ reunites Jordan Brand with the influential retailer as part of the latter’s 30th anniversary celebration. Featuring the same reimagined build the creative partners unveiled in 2020, the mid-top is exclusive to Union and drawn from a capsule — titled ‘Tent and Trail’ — inspired by outdoor gear from the’80s and ‘90s. A neutral taupe hue is applied to the upper, crafted from a blend of breathable mesh and soft suede. Bright hits of Roma Green distinguish the lower molded eyelets and heel tab, embellished with a raised Nike Air logo in Blue Fury. The vibrant hue is repeated on the collar lining and stitched fold-down tongue, a holdover detail, along with translucent TPU wings and a yellow ‘UN/LA’ tag, from the 2020 collaboration. Lightweight cushioning is provided by an off-white polyurethane midsole with an aqua-tinged Air-sole unit under the heel.

name: BAPE x 2002R 'Apes Together Strong - Grey Camo' Special Box
BAPE x 2002R 'Apes Together Strong - Grey Camo'
story: Releasing as part of the larger ‘Apes Together Strong’ collection, the BAPE x New Balance 2002R ’Grey Camo’ treats the lifestyle running shoe to a neutral makeover. Varying shades of grey are applied to the textile upper, covered in BAPE’s ABC camo print and reinforced with tonal suede overlays. Silver reflective detailing on the ‘N’ logo and wraparound shark tooth detailing offers added visibility in low-light conditions. Lightweight cushioning is provided by an off-white ABZORB midsole, supported underfoot by an N-ergy rubber outsole.

name: BAPE x 2002R 'Apes Together Strong - Black Camo'
story: Launching as part of the ‘Apes Together Strong’ capsule collection, the BAPE x New Balance 2002R ‘Camo’ dresses the retro runner in the Japanese streetwear brand’s signature flourishes. BAPE’s ABC camo in green and brown floods the textile upper, fortified with black and charcoal overlays in suede and nubuck. Silver reflective detailing is applied to the ‘N’ logo and the shark tooth detailing that wraps around the heel. The sneaker is mounted on an off-white ABZORB midsole, featuring ABZORB SBS heel cushioning for added stability.

name: BAPE x 2002R 'Apes Together Strong - Black Camo' Special Box
Neymar Jr. x Future Z 1.1 FG AG 'Jelly Bean'
New Balance 992 Paperboy Fried Egg
story: The Paperboy Paris x New Balance 992 Made in USA ‘Fried Egg’ features a subdued color scheme that reflects what the Parisian eatery calls its favorite protein ingredient. A neutral tan finish is applied to the upper, constructed from a traditional blend of breathable mesh with soft suede overlays. Stitched-on patchwork suede eyestays are rendered in a yolky yellow hue for a subtle pop of color, while the reflective ‘N’ logo offers added visibility in low-light conditions. Paperboy’s signature logo adorns the back heel.

name: Black Fives x Suede Classic Jr 'Star Sapphire'
Marimekko x Wmns Forum Low 'Laine Wave'
story: The Marimekko x adidas women’s Forum Low ‘Laine Wave’ enlivens the retro hoops shoe with vibrant bursts of color. Recycled content is built into the white synthetic leather upper, secured with an adjustable hook-and-loop ankle strap. adidas’ Trefoil logo is debossed on the Forum’s signature X-shaped overlay, covered in the Finnish design house’s wavy Laine print in magenta and Vivid Red. The latter hue is repeated on the heel overlay and durable rubber outsole. Marimekko branding decorates the sockliner and woven tongue tag.

name: Nike Dunk Low SP UNDEFEATED Canteen Dunk vs. AF1 Pack
story: Drawn from the crossover ‘Dunk vs. AF-1’ pack, the Undefeated x Nike Dunk Low ‘Canteen’ features a familiar design that recalls the ‘InsideOut Priority’ Air Force 1 collaboration from 2006. Varying shades of brown are applied to the upper, composed of smooth leather and patterned textile. Tonal leather piping surrounding the eyestay and forefoot overlay, while a bright yellow Swoosh cuts across the midfoot. Unlike its predecessor, this pair removes the printed midsole graphic that reads ‘On Your Feet Kid,’ and adds an embroidered Five Strikes logo on the lateral heel. Undefeated’s signature emblem is repeated on the woven tongue tag.

name: Reebok Classic Leather Tabi High Maison Margiela Red
story: The Maison Margiela x Reebok Classic Leather Tabi High ‘Vector Red’ applies a bold one-note finish to a modern interpretation of a vintage ‘80s silhouette. Scarlet cow leather is utilized on the upper, featuring Margiela’s Tabi split toe and a heightened collar secured with a hook-and-loop strap inspired by classic basketball shoes. The hybrid sneaker is riddled with cut-out paneling throughout the midfoot and collar, yielding an airy aesthetic that nods to gladiator sandals. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a matching red EVA midsole.

name: Club C Mid 2 Vintage 'White Bright Cobalt'
Reebok Classic Leather Tabi High Maison Margiela Bianchetto
New Balance Vision Racer Jaden Smith Grey
adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Mist
story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Mist’ is taken from the four-piece ‘Mono’ pack, which introduces a refreshed take on the flagship Yeezy sneaker. Traditional Primeknit is replaced by a monofilament mesh upper, finished in a dark beige hue and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. The sock-like one-piece upper is reinforced with an internal cage and equipped with a webbing heel tab for easy on and off. A full-length Boost midsole, wrapped in semi-translucent rubber for added support and durability, provides responsive cushioning. This shoe released exclusively in Europe, Africa, India, the Middle East, Russia, Ukraine, and China.

name: Nike Air Force 1 Low First Use Light Sail Red
Asics Gel-Trabuco 9 F/CE. x Costs Gore-Tex
adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Ice
story: The adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Ice’ represents one of four monochromatic colorways that collectively introduce a refreshed take on the minimalist silhouette. In lieu of traditional Primeknit, the upper is constructed from monofilament mesh, rendered in an icy blue shade and accented with a tonal lateral side stripe. Additional details include an interior cage, webbing heel tab and molded eyelets. A full-length Boost midsole delivers responsive cushioning. This shoe released exclusively in in North America, Latin America and China.

name: Nike Air Force 1 Low SP UNDEFEATED Ballistic Dunk vs. AF1
story: Launching as part of the ‘Dunk vs. AF-1’ pack, the Undefeated x Nike Air Force 1 Low SP ‘Ballistic’ takes direct inspiration from an ultra-limited Dunk High collaboration, initially released to friends and family in 2003, and subsequently reissued in 2013 as part of the ‘Bring Back 2003’ pack. The low-top carries a ballistic mesh upper in a subdued shade of military green, with tonal leather overlays and a contrasting black Swoosh. Undefeated’s Five Strikes logo decorates the sneaker’s lateral heel and woven tongue tag, while the insole displays ‘Dunk vs AF-1’ branding. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of an Air-sole unit nestled in the heel of the off-white midsole, supported by a black pivot-point rubber outsole.

name: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Mono Clay
story: Dropping alongside three companion colorways in a similar one-note finish, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 ‘Mono Clay’ updates the minimalist silhouette with an upper constructed from monofilament mesh. The lightweight material is rendered in a pale coral hue and reinforced with an internal cage. A webbing pull tab is affixed to the heel, lining up with tonal stripe detailing on the lateral side. The sneaker rides on a standard full-length Boost midsole with rubber-wrapped sidewalls. This shoe released exclusively in the Asia Pacific and China.

name: Nike Dunk Low UNDEFEATED Canteen Dunk vs. AF1 Pack (PS)
story: Offered in little kid sizing, the Undefeated x Nike Dunk Low SP PS ‘Canteen’ is taken from the crossover ‘Dunk vs. AF-1’ pack. The sneaker takes its cues from Undefeated’s ‘Inside Out Priority’ Air Force 1 collaboration from 2006, featuring a leather upper finished in varying shades of brown. The understated palette is enlivened by tonal prints and a contrasting hit of Lemon Frost on the leather Swoosh. Undefeated’s Five Strikes logo adorns the woven tongue tag and lateral heel.

name: Maison Margiela x Classic Leather Tabi High 'Black'
story: The Maison Margiela x Reebok Classic Leather Tabi High ‘Black’ delivers a monochromatic colorway of a hybrid silhouette inspired by gladiator sandals. This reimagining of Reebok’s 1983 Classic Leather features Margiela’s Tabi cleft toe and décortiqué technique, resulting in open-shell construction throughout the midfoot and high-cut collar. Margiela’s grid-like number logo adorns the woven tongue tag, while the fashion house’s signature embroidered detailing appears in white thread on the heel tab, along with tonal Reebok branding.

name: Reebok Classic Leather Tabi High Maison Margiela White
Nike Dunk Low UNDEFEATED Canteen Dunk vs. AF1 Pack (TD)
story: Releasing as part of the ‘Dunk vs. AF-1’ pack, the Undefeated x Nike Dunk Low SP TD ‘Canteen’ showcases a familiar design inspired by the ‘Inside Out Priority’ Air Force 1 collaboration from 2006. Varying shades of brown are applied to the leather upper, featuring a tonal shemagh print throughout the quarter panel and forefoot. A leather Swoosh in Lemon Frost delivers a vibrant pop of contrasting color, while Undefeated’s Five Strikes logo decorates the lateral heel and woven tongue tag.

name: Maison Margiela x Classic Leather Tabi High 'White'
story: The Maison Margiela x Reebok Classic Leather Tabi High ‘White’ presents a pristine colorway of a hybrid sneaker that reimagines an early ‘80s retro runner. Margiela’s signature décortiqué technique is executed on the towering silhouette, resulting in an open white leather build inspired by gladiator sandals. Additional Margiela flourishes include a Tabi split toe and stitched detailing on the heel tab. The luxury fashion house’s grid-like number logo graces the woven tongue tag. Atop the collar, an adjustable hook-and-loop strap is reminiscent of classic basketball sneakers.

name: adidas Stan Smith Kyne
story: Designed in partnership with the Japanese artist, the Kyne x adidas Stan Smith ‘White Pulse Aqua’ updates the iconic court shoe with a pristine synthetic leather made in part with recycled content. The monochromatic finish is disrupted by hits of aqua on the heel tab and debossed tongue tag, featuring traditional Stan Smith branding on the right shoe and Kyne’s original artwork on the left. The artist’s signature is stamped on the lateral heel as the finishing touch.

name: Reebok Classic Leather Tabi High Maison Margiela Black
adidas Rod Laver Noah
story: Launching as part of a capsule collection with the New York-based menswear brand, the Noah x adidas Rod Laver ‘White Green’ delivers a sustainable take on the vintage court shoe. The white mesh upper is made with recycled ocean plastic and reinforced with a tonal suede forefoot overlay. In a nod to the Long Island roots of Noah founder Brendon Babenzien, a seashell graphic adorns the leather heel tab, finished in green on the left shoe and navy blue on the right. The same mismatched colors are repeated on the rubber outsole.

name: Flex Plus TD 'Light Violet Crimson Bliss'
ZX 2K Boost 2.0 'White Semi Solar Slime'
colorway: White Tint/Semi Solar Slime/Semi Solar Slime

name: Flex Plus SE GS 'Pink Crimson Tint'
Wmns Legacy Lifter 2 'Aura Orange Boulder Grey'
Supreme x Grosso Mid 'Monogram S - Red'
story: Releasing as part of the ‘Monogram S’ pack, the Supreme x Vans Grosso Mid ‘Red’ delivers a two-tone colorway of the skate shoe named after Jeff Grosso. The upper combines red suede with canvas paneling covered in an all-over print composed of Supreme’s ‘S’ logo. ‘Grosso Forever’ is inscribed on the exterior of the black woven tongue tag, while the interior side reveals dual Vans and Supreme branding. The mid-top is mounted on a crisp white vulcanized rubber midsole, accented with a contrasting black pinstripe and supported by a waffle-traction gum rubber outsole.

name: Puma PWRFrame OP-1 Cyber High Rise Vaporous Grey
Wmns Racer TR21 'Dash Grey Clear Pink'
New Balance 992 YCMC Rewind
story: Developed in partnership with the Baltimore-based retailer, the YCMC x New Balance 992 Made In USA ‘Rewind’ presents a nostalgic collaboration inspired by ‘90s pop culture. The retro runner features a bright cyan mesh upper with suede and synthetic overlays in dark navy and purple. A silver ‘N’ logo is framed in a neon green hue, while graphic prints on the sockliner recall iconography from a ‘90s cable TV staple, ‘Yo! MTV Raps.’ The jumbled mix of colors up top are offset by a crisp white ABZORB midsole.

name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 PF 'Shattered Backboard'
story: The Jordan Why Not Zer0.4 PF ‘Shattered Backboard’ updates Russell Westbrook’s signature shoe with a distinctive palette that takes inspiration from the coveted Air Jordan 1 colorway from 2015. The upper, constructed from off-white textile with reinforced synthetic overlays in orange and black, sits atop a cushy foam midsole with double-stacked Air Zoom units in the forefoot for extra-responsive cushioning. Exclusive to Asia, this PF version utilizes an extra-durable rubber outsole designed for play on outdoor courts.

name: Nike Dunk Low Dusty Olive
story: Dressed in a buttery suede build finished in contrasting tones, the Nike Dunk Low ‘Dusty Olive’ could be mistaken for the lost fourth member of Nike’s ‘Ugly Duckling’ pack from 2001. The upper combines a rustic brown base with pale green overlays and bright orange hits on the Swoosh, heel tab and laces. A woven Nike tag decorates the lightly padded tongue, featuring the same brown nylon construction used on the collar. The multi-hued build is offset by a crisp white rubber midsole, which gives way to an outsole that delivers a final pop of color.

name: adidas Probound Noah
story: Releasing as part of a capsule collection with Brendon Babenzien’s New York-based menswear brand, the Noah x adidas Probound ‘White Blue Bird’ brings back the archival model for the first time in over 40 years. Breathable white mesh is utilized on the upper, made with recycled ocean plastic and reinforced with tonal suede overlays. Blue serrated leather three-stripes adorn the quarter panel, featuring ‘Noah’ stamped in metallic gold lettering on the rearmost stripe. An off-white rubber cupsole anchors the low-profile silhouette.

name: Supreme x Era 'Monogram S - Red'
story: The Supreme x Vans Era ‘Red’ is taken from the ‘Monogram S’ pack, featuring three colorways each of the Era and Skate Grosso Mid. Like its companion styles, this pair showcases an all-over two-tone print throughout the upper. The canvas build is lined in white leather and equipped with a PopCush insole for added impact protection and energy return. Supreme branding is limited to the red license plate at the back of the vulcanized midsole. Vans’ waffle-tread gum rubber outsole delivers superior grip.

name: Supreme x Grosso Mid 'Monogram S - Royal'
story: The Supreme x Vans Grosso Mid ‘Royal’ is one of six styles that make up the ‘Monogram S’ pack, featuring three colorways each of the Grosso Mid and Era. The mixed-material build combines royal blue suede with canvas side panels covered in a two-tone monogram print. Performance benefits include a reinforced Duracap underlay and a PopCush insole for lightweight cushioning. The mid-top rides on a vulcanized white rubber midsole, accented with a red license plate bearing a Supreme wordmark. Underfoot, Vans’ waffle traction outsole features sticky gum rubber for outstanding grip.
